402190121/http://www.emmyonline.tv/mediacenter/_pdf/day_1112_nominees_anounced_v11.pdf |archivedate=April 2, 2015 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cdn.emmyonline.org/day_39th_winners_creative.pdf |title=The National Academy of Television Arts & Sciences Announces Winners for the 39th Annual Daytime Entertainment Creative Arts Emmy\u00ae Awards |publisher=National Academy of Television Arts & Sciences |format=PDF |date=June 17, 2012 |accessdate=June 18, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The National Academy of Television Arts & Sciences Announced the 39th Annual Daytime Entertainment Emmy Awards|url=http://www.emmyonline.tv/mediacenter/_pdf/day_1112_telecast_winners.pdf|publisher=National Academy of Television Arts & Sciences|accessdate=June 25, 2012|page=4|format=PDF|date=June 23, 2012}}{{Dead link|date=June 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }}</ref>\n| [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Children's Animated Program|Outstanding Children's Animated Program]]\n| [[Bret Haaland]], [[Mark McCorkle]], [[Bob Schooley]], Nick Filippi, Chris Neuhahn, Ant Ward, [[Andrew Huebner]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Performer In An Animated Program|Outstanding Performer in an Animated Program]]\n| [[Jeff Bennett]] (for \"Kowalski\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Directing in an Animated Program\n| David Knott, Shaun Cashman, Christo Stamboliev, Steve Loter, Lisa Schaffer\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| <!-- Please do not change the proper name of this award by removing the \"Achievement in\" portion --> Outstanding Achievement in Music Direction and Composition <!-- Please do not change the proper name of this award by removing the \"Achievement in\" portion -->\n| [[Adam Berry]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Original Song \u2013 Children's and Animation\n| Adam Berry, John Behnke (for \"Off the Clock\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Original Song \u2013 Children's and Animation\n| Adam Berry, Brandon Sawyer (for \"In the Happy Little Land of 