Toys==\nDreamWorks has licensed to a number of manufacturers, including Hooga Loo Toys, who had a successful run creating a line of plush toys associated with the second Madagascar movie. Based on its success, Hooga Loo was granted a license to create an entirely new toy line for the new series. Hooga Loo recruited the creative development team, [[Pangea Corporation]], the company who assisted Playmates Toys in the development of the very successful ''[[Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles]]'', to work systemically with DreamWorks and develop toys inspired by the series.<ref>Toys and Family Entertainment Magazine</ref> The toy line included a full range of plush characters, as well as collectible figures and wacky vehicles. Fast food restaurants courted DreamWorks to glean the rights for a [[quick service restaurant|QSR]] deal, which finally materialized in late 2009. McDonald's had produced a line of toys based on the second film. This relationship forged a new deal with McDonald's.\n\nLicensed merchandise based on the show began debuting in January 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.toysrus.com/search/index.jsp?kwCatId=&kw=penguins%20of%20madagascar&origkw=penguins%20of%20madagascar&f=Taxonomy/TRUS/2254197&sr=1 |title=Toys\"R\"Us/Babies\"R\"Us |publisher=Toysrus.com |accessdate=June 10, 2010 }}{{Dead link|date=June 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }}</ref><ref name=\"news.toonzone.net\">{{cite web |url=http://news.toonzone.net/articles/32066/penguins-of-madagascar-operation-dvd-premiere-arriving-feb-9-2010 |title=Animation News Discussion Cartoon Community \u2013 toonzone news |publisher=News.toonzone.net |accessdate=June 10, 2010 }}{{Dead link|date=June 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }}</ref> In February 2010, McDonald's began their \"Mission: Play\" Happy Meal toy campaign, which featured eight toys based on the penguins in the series.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.happymeal.com/en_US/standalone.html?s=Intro&swfH=450&swfW=772&bs=toys&swf=/en_US/swf3/sections/toys/intro/intro.swf&bgc=%23000000&ID=#Intro |title=HappyMeal.com |publisher=HappyMeal.com |date=February 22, 2010 |accessdate=June 10, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100608103140/http://www.happymeal.com/en_US/standalone.html?s=Intro&swfH=450&swfW=772&bs=toys&swf=%2Fen_US%2Fswf3%2Fsections%2Ftoys%2Fintro%2Fintro.swf&bgc=%23000000&ID=#Intro |archivedate=June 8, 2010 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Video games==\n* ''[[The Penguins of Madagascar (video game)|The Penguins of Madagascar]]'' video game is a Nintendo DS action-adventure game based on the TV show of the same name. The game was released by [[THQ]] on November 2, 2010 and developed by Griptonite Games.<ref>[http://www.penguinsofmadagascarvideogame.com/ Penguins Of Madagascar the Video Game Official Site] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101118023047/http://www.penguinsofmadagascarvideogame.com/ |date=November 18, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite press release | title = 'The Penguins of Madagascar' Videogame Now Available from THQ | publisher=IGN | date = November 3, 2010 | url = http://ds.ign.com/articles/113/1132274p1.html | accessdate = 2011-09-22}}</ref>\n* ''[[The Penguins of Madagascar: Dr. Blowhole Returns \u2013 Again!]]'' was released by THQ on September 6, 2011, for Wii, Xbox 360, PlayStation 3 and Nintendo DS.<ref>{{Cite press release|title=Only Team Penguin Can Save the World From Dolphin Domination in THQ'S The Penguins of Madagascar: Dr. Blowhole Returns \u2013 Again! |publisher=[[THQ]] |date=July 21, 2011 |url=http://www.thq.com/us/go/article/view/247819/only_team_penguin_can_save_the_world_from_dolphin_domination_in_thq%E2%80%99s_the_penguins_of_madagascar:_dr._blowhole_returns_%E2%80%93_again! |accessdate=2011-09-21}}</ref>\n\n==Feature film==\n{{Main article|Penguins of Madagascar}}\nA spin-off feature film, starring the penguins from the franchise, was released on November 26, 2014.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kit|first=Borys|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/madagascar-spin-be-helmed-by-222257|title='Madagascar' Spin-Off to Be Helmed by 'Bee Movie' Co-Director (Exclusive)|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=August 11, 2011|accessdate=August 12, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Oldham|first=Stuart|last2=Maxwell|first2=Erin|title=Comic-Con: D'Works fires up 'Kung Fu Panda 3'|url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118056504|accessdate=July 12, 2012|newspaper=Variety|date=July 12, 2012}}</ref> The film takes place after the events of ''[[Madagascar 3: Europe's Most Wanted]]'', and is unrelated to the TV series, which is set in an alternate reality.<ref name=ColliderConRecap>{{cite web|last1=Goldberg|first1=Matt|title=PENGUINS OF MADAGASCAR Comic-Con Panel Recap: A Great DreamWorks Animated Film Might Be on the Way|url=http://collider.com/penguins-of-madagascar-comic-con-panel-recap/|publisher=Collider.com|accessdate=July 25, 2014|date=July 24, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Portal|Nickelodeon|Animation|Television}}\n* {{IMDb title|0892700}}\n* {{bcdb |Other_Studios/D/DreamWorks/Television/The_Penguins_Of_Madagascar/|The Penguins of Madagascar}}\n* {{tv.com show|the-penguins-of-madagascar|The Penguins of Madagascar}}\n\n{{Madagascar (franchise)}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Awards to ''The Penguins of Madagascar''\n|list=\n{{Annie Award for Best Animated Television Production}}\n{{Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Children's Animated Program}}\n{{EmmyAward AnimationLessThanHour 2001-2025}}\n}}\n{{DreamWorks animated films}}\n{{Former Nickelodeon original series}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Penguins Of Madagascar}}\n[[Category:Madagascar (franchise)]]\n[[Category:2000s Nickelodeon shows]]\n[[Category:2010s Nickelodeon shows]]\n[[Category:2000s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:2008 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2015 American television series endings]]\n[[Category