, Nick Lead Daytime Emmys' Animation Nominations |publisher=Animation Magazine |date=May 13, 2010 |accessdate=June 10, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/article/11524# |author=Karl J. Paloucek |title=Which kids' shows really DESERVE an Emmy? |publisher=Channel Guide Magazine |date=May 14, 2010 |accessdate=June 28, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cdn.emmyonline.org/day_37th_winners_creative.pdf |title=The National Academy of Television Arts & Sciences Announces Winners of the 37th Annual Daytime Entertainment Creative Arts Emmy Awards |publisher=National Academy of Television Arts & Sciences |format=PDF |date=June 25, 2010 |accessdate=June 28, 2010}}</ref>\n| Outstanding Special Class Animated Program\n| [[Bob Schooley]], [[Mark McCorkle]], [[Bret Haaland]], Dina Buteyn, Dean Hoff<br /><small>Tied with ''[[SpongeBob SquarePants]]''</small>\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| <!-- Please do not change the proper name of this award by removing the \"Achievement in\" portion --> Outstanding Achievement in Music Direction and Composition <!-- Please do not change the proper name of this award by removing the \"Achievement in\" portion -->\n| [[Adam Berry]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Writing in Animation\n| Brandon Sawyer, Bill Motz, Bob Roth, Eddie Guzelian, Bob Schooley, Mark McCorkle\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Directing in an Animated Program\n|Nicholas Filippi, Bret Haaland and Lisa Schaffer\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Reel Award (Motion Picture Sound Editors)|Golden Reel Award]]s<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mpse.org/goldenreels/2010awards/2010tvnominees.html |title=2010 Golden Reel Award Nominees: Television |publisher=[[Motion Picture Sound Editors]] |accessdate=April 22, 2011}}</ref>\n| Best Sound Editing: Television Animation\n| Episode: \"What Goes Around\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Kids' Choice Awards]]<ref name=\"Nickelodeon official site\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nick.com/kids-choice-awards/penguins-of-madagascar-cartoon.html|title=Nicke